The paper deals with the task of designing behavior diagnostic games using machine learning techniques. This involves modeling player traits and using Markov Decision Processes to parameterize the games. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on human-computer interaction and psychology, which suggests the sub-categories cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) as likely candidates. Finally, the paper involves game theory and optimization, which could place it in the sub-category cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
